Matplotlib - basic visualisation
seaborn - advanced. designed on top of matplotlib. Thats why even while using seaborn, u use matplotlib to show the plot and to add title etc.

distribution plot (histogram) - based on means

chart used for data distribution - Histogram
to find Outlier (group la doop) - Box Plot
to find co-ordinates for 2 data - line plot
to check overall data - Scatter plot
Correlation - heatmap

every chart is defined for a purpose

Correlation:
If one column value increases and other column value also increases - positive correlation
If one column value increases and other column value decreases - negative correlation
If no relation between 2 columns - 0 correlation

If we want to find the relation between 2 columns - use heatmap

Interview:
Some Model (linear regression) will be decided based on correlation. If its highly correlated, go with this model

